;; NOTA records are positional. Type, then fields, no keywords.
;; The `(key value)` shape from Lisp/Clojure/JSON is not NOTA.
;; If you're sketching a new NOTA record, read .agents/skills/nota-design/SKILL.md first.
;;
;; tier values (fourth positional field below):
;;   apex      — read once; recognise everywhere
;;   keystroke — applies on every keystroke and every report
;;   topic     — consulted when the topic comes up
;;   mechanism — procedural; consulted when the named mechanism is in play

[
  (Architecture component-triad .agents/skills/component-triad/SKILL.md Apex
    [How a component is split into daemon + thin CLI + signal-* contract, and how the Signal/Nexus/SEMA runtime carries async mail. Read when building or reasoning about a component's shape.])
  (Architecture structural-forms .agents/skills/structural-forms/SKILL.md Apex
    [The structural-macro vocabulary for defining a language as data: positional struct syntax, pipe-parenthesis generics, pipe-brace traits, the dimensional principle, and positional special forms for streams and families. Read when authoring or editing schema-next grammar shapes.])
  (Architecture contract-repo .agents/skills/contract-repo/SKILL.md Topic
    [How to shape a wire-contract crate: six-verb spine, signal_channel! macro, layered-effect pattern. Read when creating or editing a signal-* contract crate.])
