    [The standard shape for an engine situation report: component ledgers, sizes, interfaces, runtime paths, witnesses, introspection tools. Read when writing up an engine's current state.])
  (Architecture language-design .agents/skills/language-design/SKILL.md Topic
    [The discipline for designing a language or typed-record tree: closed enums, structural beauty over ad-hoc strings, branches/leaves vocabulary. Read when shaping a new language or record grammar.])
  (Architecture library .agents/skills/library/SKILL.md Topic
    [How to decide when to extract a library crate from a daemon, and where the library/daemon line falls. Read when a daemon holds reusable logic that wants its own crate.])
  (Architecture subscription-lifecycle .agents/skills/subscription-lifecycle/SKILL.md Topic
    [The close-vs-retract semantics and token-keyed cleanup for subscriptions. Read when designing subscription teardown.])

  (Craft abstractions .agents/skills/abstractions/SKILL.md Keystroke
    [The verb-belongs-to-noun rule: put logic in methods on data-bearing types, never a free helper where a method would do. Applies on every Rust edit.])
  (Craft enum-contact-points .agents/skills/enum-contact-points/SKILL.md Apex
    [How to express engine logic as enum-vs-enum cross-product matching: name the contact point as a nested match or trait, not scattered arms, string predicates, or flag soup. Read when writing an engine's load-bearing branching.])
  (Craft naming .agents/skills/naming/SKILL.md Keystroke
    [The full-English-words rule plus the offender table of forbidden abbreviations. Applies on every identifier you write.])
  (Craft secrets .agents/skills/secrets/SKILL.md Keystroke
    [How to handle secret values when an authorized task needs plaintext: keep them transient and out of chat, reports, logs, commits, traces, the Nix store, and checked-in files; prefer gopass, sops-nix, and blind pipe-to-sink. Read when a task touches tokens or other secrets.])
  (Craft privacy .agents/skills/privacy/SKILL.md Keystroke
    [How to keep private personal-affairs work off public workspace surfaces and out of privacy Zero Spirit, defaulting to private repositories. Read when a prompt or artifact touches personal affairs.])
